article.headline: Fairleigh Dickinson 85, Canisius 83, 2OT
article.story: HACKENSACK, N.J. (AP) -- Andre Harris hit two free throws midway through the second overtime period and Fairleigh Dickinson held on for an 85-83 win over Canisius on Saturday night. After Cameron Tyler tied the game at 72-72 by hitting the second of two free throws with 1:08 left in regulation, the teams traded scores in the first overtime before Manny Ubilla hit two free throws with 1:16 left to put the Knights (2-4) ahead 80-79. However, Menghe A'Nyam tied it by hitting the second of two foul shots with 44 seconds left. The teams then traded free throws in the second overtime before Harris scored the eventual game-winning points with 2:04 to play. The Golden Griffins (2-4) had two late chances to win the game, but Frank Turner missed two free throws and a jumper in the final minute. Corey Herring had a game-high 26 points for Canisius, while Turner finished with 19 points, four assists and five steals. Harris led FDU with 24 points, shooting 7-of-13 from the floor, while Tyler and Ubilla both added 19 points.
